The only household thing that works is hot koolaid. Bruh, you’ll cut it out before it fades out.

How to: mix a packet into water, but not the entire amount called for, the less water, the brighter the color, make sure it’s hot (like boiled/steaming hot), dip in lightened hair for 10 min, it’ll be there for 6 months and smell fruity for 2 weeks.

snippet.textDisplay: K. So I absolutely know this work cause I’ve done it before. If you’re too lazy to go to the store and have vinegar and hair dye. Boil the vinegar and add color of choice. While it’s still boiling dip hair into it for 10 minutes. Wash out after 10 minutes. Works on brown and blonde hair. I did it when I wanted to rebel and didn’t have a way to get hair dye. It works best for dip dying hair.. not saying do it. But I mean.... it works.. and it’s extremely vibrant. It works best with red dye.
